ngcp-klish-config 
=================

Sipwise NGCP shell based on klish/clish


WARNING:
=======

The status is work-in-progress. Do not expect a full blown shell just yet!


BASIC HOW-TO:
============

1) Clone & Install the system & software requirements:
    - NGCP-CLISH (https://github.com/sipwise/klish)
    - LUA-URI (https://github.com/sipwise/lua-uri.git)

2) Clone & Deploy NGCP-KLISH-CONFIG in your /etc (launch script + clish directory)
    # /etc/cli.sh
    # /etc/clish
    
3) Add execution permisions to the launcher if needed, ie:
    # chmod +x /etc/cli.sh

4) Create a dedicated system user (ie: cliuser) with password and default shell: /etc/cli.sh
    # cliuser:x:1001:1001:,,,:/dev/null:/etc/cli.sh


5) Modify /etc/sudoers to allow cliuser to execute enable mode calls. For example:

    Defaults:cliuser targetpw
    cliuser ALL=(ALL) /usr/bin/clish



BASIC USAGE:
===========

1) SSH to the system as 'cliuser' using the new account or manually launch /etc/cli.sh

2) Use tab/autocompletion and ? to explore the available menus and commands

3) Enter ENABLE to start priviledged mode, use the system's root password when asked for one

cliuser@localhost's password:
